About this item

Description

Slip resistant non marking outsole. High density removable foam insole with arch support. Lightweight shoe that offers great support. Man made upper can be easily cleaned with soap and water. Medium height offers exception comfort and support. Generous toe box allows for a comfortable fit all day long. Padded collar is comfortable to the touch.

Customer reviews

3.7 out of 5 stars3.7 out of 5
4,567 global ratings

Customers say

Customers find these nursing shoes classy for work, with good arch support that provides lower back support, and consider them good value for money. The fit and comfort receive mixed feedback - while some find them comfortable, others report they run small and make feet hurt. Moreover, durability is also mixed, with some saying they break in well while others report the shoes falling apart. Additionally, customers describe the shoes as very stiff, with one noting they feel like fake plastic.

    4.0 out of 5 starsVerified Purchase
    THEY FIT!!!
    Reviewed in the United States on January 5, 2024
    Size: 9Color: Brown Tool
    1:10
    UPDATE: Important stuff first: I measured from the inside of the shoe from toe to heel on each size I have. 8.5 regular measures 10" long 9 regular measures 10 " long My foot measures 9 " long and 9 " around the widest part of my... See more
    UPDATE:
    Important stuff first:
    I measured from the inside of the shoe from toe to heel on each size I have.
    8.5 regular measures 10" long
    9 regular measures 10 " long
    My foot measures 9 " long and 9 " around the widest part of my foot. If your foot is wider/thicker than this I recommend you get the wide. They're a wee bit tight around the top of my foot, but I'm hopeful they will stretch just a bit with wear.
    I placed a new order for the 8.5, my normal size, and I'm so happy because they fit!
    I don't know why the seller doesn't list this information. They never responded to my inquiry, nor did the manufacturer when I contacted them directly by email. I printed the foot measurement tool on their website, verified the inches on the paper were accurate, I measured a size 10! Lol! Not even close since the 9s were flopping on my feet. Don't look for product support from seller or manufacturer. You're on your own if you buy these. Good thing the return policy is awesome! I'll be keeping the 8.5 & returning the 9's to my local UPS store.

    ORIGINAL REVIEW:
    I ordered a size 9, instead of a size 8.5 like usual, because reviewers said these run small. They fit width wise, but their too long and the heel slips when I walk. They want to be like flip flops. I wish the sellers would put the measurement of the inside of the shoe so we could order based on our foot measurement. I'm so bummed I have to send these back. I got a great deal on them & they're so cute. Oh well.
    My suggestion is if you have thick feet, these clogs will be tight on you across the top of your foot. The insoles are quite beefy and make the shoe comfortable if you're on your feet all day. I'd say these shoes are made for more narrow feet. If you suffer from swelling at the end of the day I suggest you try the wide width.

    I don't dislike anything about this chunky style shoe. I did down size since the heel height is about 1.5 inches. I go up a size for toe room on a 2 inch heel.
